blockStates.name: Visualize Binary Functions
blockStates.userText:
Contour plots can be used to
visualize binary functions such 
as Himmelblau's function:

f(x, y) = (x²+y-11)² + (x+y²-7)²

This function has four local
minima and one local maximum.

A Contour2D Block accepts
a 2D array from a Binary 
Function Block. You will need
to specify this output type for
the Binary Function Block as
its default output is a 1D array. 
Six ports X0, DX, NX, Y0, DY, 
and NY accept the beginning x 
and y coordinates, the increments
in x and y directions, and the
number of steps in the two 
directions.

blockStates.name: Note
blockStates.userText:
Be sure to set the output 
type of this block to 2D.
